<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{wa}}}} is a sentence ending particle mainly used by women.
</p>

@BGRNDSTART{{}}
@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@HI{{@EM{{wa}}}} indicates emotion or feelings of admiration

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{now^night}}no@KT{{opera}}ha,@KJ{{book^hit}}nisubarashikatta@EM{{wa}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Tonight's concert was absolutely fabulous.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@HI{{@EM{{wa}}}} softens the tone of a statement.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{hokano@KJ{{store}}de@KJ{{buy}}ttano@KJ{{direction}}gaiito@KJ{{think}}u@EM{{wa}}}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I think it would be better to buy it from another store.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@HI{{@EM{{wa}}}} has the same pronunciation as the topic marker <a href="grammar-particle-wa.html">@HI{{ha}}</a>
but is written with a different hiragana character.
</p>

