<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{wa}}}} can follow any declarative sentence but cannot follow volitional forms of verbs and cannot follow questions.
</p>

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{wa}}}} can occur with other sentence-ending particles, such as <a href="grammar-particle-ne.html">@HI{{ne}}</a>
and <a href="grammar-particle-yo.html">@HI{{yo}}</a>. In such cases @HI{{@EM{{wa}}}} must precede these particles.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}hamo@KJ{{going}}ku@EM{{wa}}yo.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I'll go there too. (<em>Emphatic</em>)
  </td> </tr>
</table>

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}hamo@KJ{{going}}ku@EM{{wa}}ne.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I'll go there too, OK?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

